From a524c96f4b21b2dec73b2ef4ebf32a359b4985dc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: User-3090 <71881005+User-3090@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 08:02:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/8] fix: preserve the outer terminal cursor color

Include OSC 12 in the host color query, consume its reply in the foreground
client, and use the reported color for software cursor rendering. Retain that
original color through redraws and restore it on normal exit and panic instead
of leaving a child-selected or reset cursor color behind.

The serialized color-kind extension rides on protocol 18 introduced by patch
0001, which is already newer than the latest released protocol 17.

Fork-Ref: 978275825634b5862555e00bbf11ecf9fcac4a6c; da3dc412cbbe06dc42f7a6d9d4a8503581293fa4; f3fac551ece1b3f05276bb60f33ed16fbd487f70
